[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426490&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426490&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Say I have mail for mockapetris@isi.arpa and the responses to
my MAILA query about isi.arpa are
	MAILD f.isi.arpa
	MAILF a.isi.arpa
&gt;From the additional records I can get the addresses, but what
goes in the rcpt command?

If I use the mail delivery record?
1)	&lt;mockapetris@isi.arpa&gt;
2)	&lt;mockapetris@f.isi.arpa&gt;

If I use the mail forwarding record?
3)	&lt;mockapetris@isi.arpa&gt;
4)	&lt;@a.isi.arpa:mockapetris@isi.arpa&gt;

(1) and (3) seem to require hosts to accept names other than
their own.  (2) might lead to conflicts if mockapetris@f.isi.arpa
isn't the same person as mockapetris@isi.arpa.

The responses to MAILB queries raise the same sort of questions.

(Sorry if I've overlooked this is my passes through the rfc's.)

Thanks,

Ron Stanonik
stanonik@nprdc.arpa

